From Mark Dubin Subject Re ringing ears jfare Jim Fare writes A friend of mine has a trouble with her ears Folks do we have an FAQ on tinnitus yet As a lo o o ong time sufferer of tinnitus and as a neuroscientist who has looked over the literature carefully I believe the following are reasonable conclusions Millions of people suffer from chronic The cause it not There is no accepted treatment that cures Some experimental treatments may have helped some people a bit but there have be no reports even anecdotal of massive good results with any of these experimental Some people with chronic loud tinnitus use noise blocking to get to Sudden onset loud tinnitus can be caused by injuries and sometimes abates or goes away after a few Aspirin is well known to exacerbate tinnitus in some There is a national association of tinnitus sufferers in the One usually gets used to Especially when concentrating on something else the tinnitus becomes Stress and lack of sleep make tinnitus more annoying I'm sure those of us who have it wish there was a cure but there is Mark dubin the ol' professor